JOHANNESBURG - Bheki Cele says the ANC's national executive committee (NEC) is to blame for the problems plaguing the party. Cele says he's embarrassed to be part of that committee. He was speaking in Pretoria on Tuesday night.  WATCH: Khoza resignation greeted with regret Cele says he's disappointed at Kebby Maphatsoe's remarks following Makhosi Khoza's departure. "I was never a member of the ANC that tells people to go away. I was very disappointed to hear Kebby Maphatsoe saying Makhosi Khoza's departure is good riddance....we cannot be the part that members ANC must go away from the ANC. You can tell people to go away from your spaza shop, not from the ANC," said Cele. eNCA